GE-AB.name: Abkhazia
GE-AB.description: The Government Republic of Abkhazia is, according to Abkhazia, Russia, Venezuela, and a few other countries, its own country, and according to everyone else, it's just the westmost part of Georgia. Russian tourists can visit without even needing a passport!

food.name: Kystybyi
food.description: A milk and flour-based flatbread fried with a mashed potato filling. I generally do not like the texture of mashed potatoes, but they were good in this. I learned the hard way that you cannot easily grate onions in a garlic press without breaking it.

diet.description: Milk is an integral part of this recipe. You can probably use a vegan milk alternative.
Flour is used to make the dough.

food.name: Red Ajika
food.description: A spicy salsa made with lots of aromatic ingredients. It went well with the kystybyi and has also proven delicious on other foods like cream cheese rangoons and chicken nuggets.

diet.description: It's spicy. I only used one habanero in my recipe, so you can make it mild if your spice tolerance is as low as mine.
This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

AF.name: Afghanistan
AF.description: The Islamic Republic of Afghanistan is a South Asian country. If you're from the United States like me, you may know it as the country we invaded almost two decades ago and then left to disastrous yet unsurprising results.
AF.motto: "There is no God but Allah; Muhammad is the messenger of Allah."

food.name: Afghani Burger
food.description: Mostly french fries wrapped in Afghan bread. Can't go wrong with a recipe that's largely french fries. Aside from the fries, I mostly just filled them with leftover mantu filling. Dipped in mango chutney, they were very satisfying chomps.

diet.description: Meat is a recommended filling for this recipe. I used a vegan ground beef substitute without issue.
This dish contains flatbread.
Hard-boiled eggs are a recommended filling for this recipe, but I did not add any to mine.

food.name: Mantu
food.description: Steamed dumplings. The yogurt, mint, tomato, onion and coriander together were a very new flavor combination for me. Took a while to make, but was very delicious.

diet.description: Lamb or ground beef is an integral part of the recipe. I used a vegan ground beef substitute without issue.
The yogurt dip unsurprisingly contains yogurt. The dumplings themselves have no dairy in them, so you can use a different dairy-free dip if you'd like.
Flour is used to make the dough.

AL.name: Albania
AL.description: The Republic of Albania is a Mediterranean European country. Wikipedia calls them a 'developing country' but their citizens don't have to file bankruptcy for medical debts very often, which is not true for the people of my country, so, like, if they have that and they're still "developing" what does that make us?
AL.motto: "You Albania, give me honour, give me the name Albanian."

food.name: Fergesë Tiranës me piperka
food.description: I'm still not entirely sure what this is. My best guess is it's some sort of casserole or creamy dip of some sort, for like bread I guess? As a dip, it is very rich and delicious. If it's not a dip, then I accidentally made something delicious.

diet.description: Cheese and yogurt are an integral part of this recipe.
Flour is used to make a roux.

food.name: Flija
food.description: Layered pancakes. Very time consuming to make, and timing is key - if you don't cook each layer just right, you'll fuck up and have some layers be way too soft and others be way too crispy like I did. Getting each layer to be similar in thickness is also an important thing I failed to do correctly. Tasted like a pancake, but with layers. Not bad, but I'm not convinced that it can beat a good old fashioned waffle, even if I made it right.

diet.description: Butter is an integral part of this recipe, and yogurt, clotted cream, and sour cream are all recommended.
Flour is used to make the dough.

music.name: The Bloody Foreigners - N'deti
music.translation: The Bloody Foreigners - Chilling at the Beach

music.name: Eugent Bushpepa - Fjalet E Qiririt
music.translation: Eugent Bushpepa - The Words of the Candle

music.name: Ingrit Gjoni ft. Gjeto Luca - Fustani Pika Pika
music.translation: Ingrit Gjoni ft. Gjeto Luca - Polka-dotted Dress

DZ.name: Algeria
DZ.description: The People's Democratic Republic of Algeria is a Northern African country on the Mediterranean coast. It is the largest country in Africa, and it houses many refugees from the neighboring Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic, which is still considered to be Moroccan territory by Morocco.
DZ.motto: "By the people and for the people."

food.name: Kanafeh
food.description: This is a dish made of phyllo dough stuffed with cheese, baked, and topped with a sugar syrup. It tastes exactly like you'd expect it to taste, which is a good thing. Highly recommended for people who don't want to worry about their roommates coming home to see them sitting down naked in the middle of the kitchen dipping a cheese wheel in maple syrup.

diet.description: Various cheeses and butter are integral to this recipe.
This recipe uses phyllo dough.

food.name: Shakshouka
food.description: It's very tomatoey and eggy. Dipping bread into it is a good choice. I think you can eat it without a bread to dip in it, but I can't handle that much tomato without something else to balance it out.

diet.description: You can make this dish without eggs, but then you're eating an egg dish without eggs.
This dish optionally uses feta cheese.

music.name: Dahmane El Harrachi - Hassebni Khoud Krak

AD.name: Andorra
AD.description: The Principality of Andorra is a microstate ruled by the French President and also the Spanish Bishop of Urgell. For some reason. One of the few countries to never be invaded by the British.

food.name: Calçot
food.description: Incredibly hard and messy to eat. But also delicious. I used Mexican grilling onions, since the internet told me those were close enough to actual calçots.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

food.name: Romesco
food.description: I definitely messed up on this because my version was very chunky and not very saucy. Despite this, it was still very tasty. Ramen mixed with Romesco and topped with onions is also very delicious.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
This recipe uses almonds.
This recipe contains bread for texture.

food.name: Torrija
food.description: Definitely not French Toast™. Crispy outside, creamy inside. Less of an eggy taste than regular French Toast, which is a plus in my book. A rich tasty treat.

diet.description: This recipe is bread.
The bread must be soaked in milk.
You better believe you're dipping it in eggs, too.

music.name: Marta Roure - Jugarem a Estimar-nos
music.translation: Marta Roure - We'll Be Playing at Loving Each Other

AO.name: Angola
AO.description: The Republic of Angola is a West African country bordering the Atlantic Ocean. Its economy is one of the fastest growing in the world (the power of oil), but said economic growth is largely benefiting a minority of the country while most people remaining in poverty (the power of oil).

food.name: Cocada Amarela
food.description: Coconutty pudding. The coconut flakes made its texture unlike most puddings. Tasty stuff.

diet.description: Egg yolk is a central part of this recipe.

food.name: Moamba de Galinha
food.description: Chicken cooked in a red palm oil sauce. I cannot accurately describe the taste of red palm oil, but it was definitely a very new taste and I'm pretty sure I enjoyed it. Chicken is tasty.

diet.description: This recipe calls for red palm oil. Please make sure you are buying sustainable palm oil if you make this recipe.
It can be a bit spicy due to all the red peppers. You can use less of them or replace with bell peppies and it'll still be good.
Chicken meat is a central ingredient in this recipe, however, the sauce itself is vegan (if you use a vegan boullion) and can be used on non-meat things.

music.name: Dog Murras ft. Noitre & Dia - Chacule Bum Dance (Magia)
Yola Araújo - Sja Paixona
music.translation: Yola Araújo - If I Already Fell in Love

AG.name: Antigua and Barbuda
AG.description: Antigua and Barbuda consists of two major islands and a bunch of smaller islands. It gained sovereignty from Britain in 1981, but still remains a member of the Commonwealth.

food.name: Antiguan Butter Bread
food.description: Very tasty and buttery. The linked recipe omits a few important details - namely the amount of flour to use. I used 360g (3 cups) and altered steps 1 and 2 as follows: mix JUST the buttermilk, yeast, and sugar, then mix the butter into the flour, THEN mix the yeast mix into the flour. After that the recipe worked great.

diet.description: BUTTERbread.
ButterBREAD.

food.name: Ducana
food.description: These were very filling. They felt like some sort of protein or energy bar. Tasty warm and tasty cold. Definitely a good way to fill up on something somewhat healthy. I did not prepare the salt fish referenced in this recipe due to fish allergies and I did not add raisins to the ducana because I love myself.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
This recipe uses flour to keep the dumplings together. Maybee some other starch would work too, so maybe give it a try if you want!

music.name: King Short Shirt - Nobody Go Run Me

AR.name: Argentina
AR.description: The Argentine Republic is the second largest country in South America and the largest Spanish-speaking nation in the world. It is currently in some land disputes for a couple islands with the United Kingdom (because of course they are) despite the fact that the islands are nowhere near the UK and are right next to Argentina. Old habits die hard, eh, Her Majesty?

food.name: Chimichurri
food.description: This sauce has a very strong herb flavor. Probably due to the fact that it's mostly parsley and oregano. Very tasty. Good with empanadas and meat.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

food.name: Empanadas Mendocinas
food.description: Delicious. Absolutely delicious. The spice mix for the meat was great. The onions were great. The crunch was great. All great. Five stars.

diet.description: Flour is the main ingredient in the dough.
This recipe uses butter and milk. You can replace the milk with water and can probably replace the butter with some other fat.
{ type: "Egg", desc: "Egg yolk is an ingredient in the dough, and egg is used for an egg wash and optionally for sealing the empanadas." }
Ground beef is an integral part of the recipe. You can use a vegetarian substitute if you want, or just use something else entirely.

food.name: Locro
food.description: It's mostly potatoes, sweet potatoes, corn, and onions. That's like the four food groups right there, so I give this stew a 4/4.

diet.description: This recipe calls for a lot of different kinds of meat.

music.name: La Fanfarria del Capitán - Bella Ciao
Gilda - No me Arrepiento de este Amor

AM.name: Armenia
AM.description: The Republic of Armenia is a country in Western Asia. It was the first country to adopt Christianity as its official religion.

food.name: Eetch
food.description: A salad made mostly of bulgur wheat. Can be served hot or cold, and it's tasty either way.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

food.name: Spas
food.description: Unsurprisingly, this minty yogurt soup tastes a lot like minty yogurt. I have a cold so hopefully eating this will cure me.

diet.description: This soup contains both flour and wheat.
The primary ingredient in this soup is Greek yogurt.
This soup contains egg yolk, but it is an optional ingredient that is not included if serving the soup cold.

AM-AR.name: Artsakh
AM-AR.description: The Republic of Artsakh, according to most countries, is part of Azerbaijan. Three other unrecognized countries, as well as various states in the USA recognize it as its own country. Despite being considered part of Azerbaijan by most of the world, it is predominantly populated by Armenians, and Armenian is the region's official language. Meetings between Armenia, Azerbaijan, and Russia began in 2021 in an attempt to Figure Things Out™.

food.name: Dolma
food.description: Although the usual image of a dolma involves grape leaves (at least where I'm from), they can also be made with fresh vegetables like bell peppers, so I made both varieties. The grape leaf ones were a bit bitter and briney, but otherwise it was all pretty tasty.

diet.description: This recipe calls for ground meat. You can use a vegan substitute or just go all-in on the rice and it'll be fine. It also calls for chicken broth, but you can use vegetable broth.
The linked recipe calls for an egg for binding, but most recipes I've found don't, so you can probably omit it.
This recipe uses pine nuts, but they're optional.

food.name: Zhingyalov hats
food.description: What happens when you make some dough and fill it with every green food you can find in your kitchen? This. A very tasty herby bread with every flavor in every bite!

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
Flour is used to make the dough.

AU.name: Australia
AU.description: The Commonwealth of Australia is best known for the fact that every wild animal on the mainland will kill you. It was doing great until the British showed up and decided it'd be a good place to put all their criminals.

food.name: Burger with the Lot
food.description: If you don't like pineapples, fried eggs, or beetroot, this dish might not be for you. If you dislike all three of those things, then you might be me, and maybe you should go back in time and tell yourself not to make this dish.

diet.description: It's a hamburger. Canadian bacon is also a topping.
The buns contain gluten.
Cheese is one of the toppings on this burger.
A fried egg is one of the toppings on this burger. Mayonnaise is one of the optional sauces.

food.name: Meat Pie
food.description: Juicy flaky meaty goodness. A perfect pastry. If you want to make the pie crust from scratch, I used this recipe for the bottom dough and this recipe for the top.

diet.description: It's called a meat pie for a reason, mate.
The pie crust uses a lot of flour.
The pie crust uses a LOT of butter.
An egg wash is applied to the top of the pie before baking.
The filling contains Worcestershire Sauce, which often has soy sauce in it.
The filling contains Worcestershire Sauce, which can have anchovies in it. I was able to easily find an anchovy-free bottle in a regular grocery store.

music.name: Shane Howard ft. Archie Roach - Back to Culture

AT.name: Austria
AT.description: The Republic of Austria is a landlocked country in Central Europe. One time their archduke got assassinated and it sort of sparked a mild war. It wasn't that big of a deal, and after it ended, everyone agreed to never have a war like that again. Everybody kept this promise. Especially the Germans.

food.name: Beef Goulash
food.description: A very strongly spiced stew. Warm, delicious, and very filling. If I lived somewhere that actually had noticable weather changes between seasons, I would definitely eat this during the winter.

diet.description: It ain't kale goulash.

food.name: Liptauer
food.description: A tasty and somewhat spicy cheese spread. The spiciness was countered by the cheesiness, so it added a nice creamy kick to the bread I spread it on.

diet.description: Cheese and butter are the main ingredients of this spread.

food.name: Vienna Bread
food.description: Because I am bad with yeast, the recipe I made can more accurately be described as Vienna breadsticks. Fortunately, size didn't matter and these bread babies were soft and delicious.

diet.description: It's bread.
Butter is an important ingredient in this bread.
An egg wash is applied prior to baking.

music.name: Dornenreich - Wer hat Angst von Einsamkeit?
music.translation: Kingdom of Thorns - Who's Afraid of Loneliness?

music.name: Visions of Atlantis - The Deep & The Dark

AZ.name: Azerbaijan
AZ.description: The Republic of Azerbaijan toes the border between Europe and Asia. They declared their independence in 1918, then got incorporated into the Soviet Union a couple years later. Now they're back to being their own country until the Soviet Union II: Electric Boogaloo drops.

food.name: Ayran
food.description: A very refreshing beverage. I preferred it without mint on top, though.

diet.description: It's basically watered down yoghurt.

food.name: Dushbara
food.description: A very tasty tortellini-esque soup. Another prime example of how mint and meat are a good combination.

diet.description: The primary ingredient of the filling is beef, and meat broth is used.
Flour is used in the dough.
Egg is used in the dough.

food.name: Shekerbura
food.description: The cardamom is a very nice touch, but otherwise these are basically just almondy biscuits.

diet.description: Flour is used in the dough.
Butter is used in the dough.
Egg is used in the dough.
Almond meal is used in the filling.

music.name: Aygü Kazımova ft. Snoop Dogg - Coffee From Colombia
Miri Yusif ft. DJ Matuya - Bomba Kimi
music.translation: Miri Yusif ft. DJ Matuya - Like a Bomb

BS.name: The Bahamas
BS.description: The Commonwealth of The Bahamas are an island nation in the Caribbean. They are the reason the Baha Men and, thus, the song 'Who Let the Dogs Out?' exist.

food.name: Bahamian Macaroni and Cheese
food.description: A very rich and filling baked macaroni and cheese dish. This ain't your mamma's macaroni and cheese, unless your mother is from the Bahamas, then it probably is.

diet.description: Butter, cheese, and evaporated milk are used in this recipe.
Egg is used for keeping things together.
Macaroni usually has flour with gluten in it. If you can find/make gluten-free macaroni, then all is well.
It can be spicy, but you can adjust how much pepper you want to use.

food.name: Guava Duff
food.description: The combination of boiled dough with mashed up guavas is very interesting. The combination of creamed butter and sugar to make the sauce is very delicious. I will definitely be using it on many non-duff foods.

diet.description: Milk and butter are used in the dough and the sauce.
Egg is used in the dough.
Flour is used in the dough.
Rum or brandy are used in the sauce, but you can substitute with vanilla.

food.name: Switcha
food.description: Unsurprisingly it tastes like sweet, citrussy, and sour water. It is a bit refreshing but probably not the best thing to drink at night like I just did. Who needs sleep anyway?

diet.description: This bevvy is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

music.name: Julien Believe ft. Bunji Garlin - Live and Wine
K.B. - Boy U Don't Know Me Eh?

BH.name: Bahrain
BH.description: The Kingdom of Bahrain is an Asian island country and the first post-oil economy in the Persian Gulf. Its capital is Manama, not to be confused with Mah Nà Mah Nà.

food.name: Balaleet
food.description: If you want to have pasta for breakfast, but also want to have tons of sugar in your breakfast, balaleet has got you covered. Also, a tablespoon of cardamom is a lot, so if you're like me and think you're too cool to buy pre-ground cardamom, reconsider before making this recipe; it'll take a while to de-shell all that 'mom.

diet.description: Vermicelli is usually made with wheat flour.
Half of this dish is made with scrambled eggs or an omelette. You can omit this if you just want some sweet noodles.

food.name: Chicken Machboos
food.description: There were a lot of flavors in this, and I think this may have been some of the best chicken I've ever eaten. I never would have thought to put cinnamon on chicken, but now I know the truth: it's tasty.

diet.description: It's chicken.
Butter is added to the rice. You can probably skip this or add a vegan substitute with no issue.

BD.name: Bangladesh
BD.description: The People's Republic of Bangladesh is a country in South Asia. It was part of British India when that was a thing, but fortunately the British eventually fucked off so now instead of dealing with "British occupation" the Bangladeshi people can instead deal with "the aftermath of British occupation."

food.name: Chomchom
food.description: Fresh cheese curds boiled in sugar syrup, stuffed with a sugary milk goo. I love milk but I was still not sold on this. The texture is uncomfortable.

diet.description: These things are almost entirely made of milk. If you don't eat dairy, this recipe is definitely not for you.
Flour is an optional binding agent.

food.name: Mughlai Paratha
food.description: Unsurprisingly, a recipe that involves lots of spiced cheese in a fried dough wrapper is absolutely delicious.

diet.description: This dish contains paneer cheese.
Wheat flour is used to make the dough.

BB.name: Barbados
BB.description: Barbados is an island country in the West Indies. They're still part of the Commonwealth, and are well known for inventing the international pop star and diplomat Her Excellency Dr. Rihanna.

food.name: Bajan Chicken and Potato Roti
food.description: A winning combination of chicken, potato, jerk seasoning, and flatbread. I burnt my hand a bit when I was cooking the roti. Worth it.

diet.description: Chicken.
Butter can be used in the dough, but other types of shortening work, too.
Flour is used in the dough.
Peppies are used. You can use less spicy peppers, or no peppers at all, if that's how you want to roll.

food.name: Bajan Pepper Sauce
food.description: A nice spicy sauce. It's heavily turmeric'd, which gave it a great flavor that many hot sauces lack, so even if you aren't huge on spicy-for-the-sake-of-spicy, it's a nice flavorful sauce.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
It's called Pepper Sauce for a reason, buddy.

food.name: Bajan Salt Bread
food.description: It's a pretty solid bread. Good for sandwiches, which is what I used it for. Because I am a fool, mine was a bit more dense than it's supposed to be, but you can avoid this problem by not being bad at baking.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
Flour is used in the dough.

food.name: Cheese Cutter
food.description: Composed of Bajan Salt Bread, Bajan Pepper Sauce, and cheddar cheese. A solid cheese sandwich. You can't go wrong with a cheese sandwich. Who doesn't like a cheese sandwich? Everybody wants a cheese sandwich.

diet.description: Flour is used in the bread dough.
It's a cheese sandwich.
The sauce is spicy. You can just not add the pepper sauce, or tone down the pepper like I did.

music.name: Krosfyah ft. Khiomal - Start De Madness
Charles D. Lewis - Another Friday Night

BY.name: Belarus
BY.description: The Republic of Belarus is a country in Eastern Europe. They like potatoes as all good boys should. Their president reigned from 1994 to 2020, and his victory in the 2020 election has been disputed. As of November 2021 he remains in power, having silenced much of his opposition.

food.name: Draniki
food.description: Potato pancakes. I don't know what I did wrong but I somehow managed to completely ruin a frying pan making these. Pro-tip: don't do that.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

food.name: Kalduny
food.description: Dumplings and/or stuffed pancakes, full of meat and onion. They're like Uncrustables® sealed crustless sandwiches, but with more potato.

diet.description: They're stuffed with meat. You can put something else in them, though.
Egg is used in the dough.
Flour is used in the dough, but might not be necessary.

BE.name: Belgium
BE.description: The Kingdom of Belgium is a country in Western Europe. The Global Peace Index considers it one of the most peaceful countries in the world, and it has very high standards of living, which means they're probably all a bunch of no-good commies.

food.name: Liège Waffles
food.description: These were without a doubt the best waffles I have ever eaten, and perhaps one of the best sweet dough-based foods I've ever eaten, too. They were rich, crisp, caramelly, and delicious all around. If you have a free weekend and can get your hands on three different kinds of flour and a few other very specific ingredients, making these beautiful babies would be an excellent use of that time. The man behind waffle-recipes.com (site defunct as of November 2021) is a waffle genius. Usually when I make a complicated or time-consuming dish I think "that was good, but too much effort to make again." With these, they were a lot of effort, but it was all worth it.

diet.description: This recipe calls for three different kinds of flour. It's safe to say there is gluten.
Cultured/European-style Butter is used in the dough.
Eggs are used in the dough.
Orange Blossom Honey is used in the dough.

food.name: Rijstevlaai
food.description: If you've ever looked at rice pudding and wished it was baked in a pie crust, then your prayers have been answered by rijstevlaai, which is literally just that. I've never had rice pudding at all before, so the texture was an interesting new experience. The creaminess was appreciated. Pie crust is always good, so that was an added bonus.

diet.description: Flour is used in the dough.
Butter is used in the dough, and the filling is mostly just milk.
Egg is used in the dough and filling.

music.name: Diablo Blvd - The Future Will Do What It's Told

BZ.name: Belize
BZ.description: Belize is a country in Central America. It's nice to have a country with just a one word name, y'know? It ain't the Kingdom of Belize. It's not the People's Democratic Republic of Belize and Friends. It's not the Adventures of Belize. Just Belize. Barbados and Antigua and Barbuda are like that, too, so maybe it's a Caribbean thing? Anyway, Belize is a cool place, and the only country to be in the Caribbean Community, Community of Latin American and Caribbean States, Central American Integration System, AND the Commonwealth, because Britain can't leave anything alone.

food.name: Chicken Legs Recado Rojo
food.description: I accidentally spilled a bunch of the recado rojo braising liquid onto the door of my oven when I tried putting it in there. I should clean that soon. The end result was tasty, though, so it was probably worth it. Also I didn't have chicken legs so I used chicken breasts, so hopefully I don't go to chicken jail for my crimes.

diet.description: Surprise! This chicken dish has meat in it!

food.name: Fry Jacks
food.description: You make some dough and then you fry the dough and then you eat the dough and it is a good tasty thing you can eat with honey or cheese or jam or any other good thing. That's what this is. I got two delicious breakfasts out of it, served with honey the first time and with, uh, cheese puffs, the second time.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
Flour is used in the dough.

food.name: Recado Rojo
food.description: A sauce that, given its name, is probably supposed to be much more red than what I made. It was still very tasty though. I used it on chicken and then later mixed some of it with some Ranch dressing to make a much better Ranch dressing.

diet.description: This sauce is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

music.name: Andy Palacio - Gi mi Punta Rock
Bella Carib - I AM HURRICANE BELLA

BJ.name: Benin
BJ.description: The Republic of Benin is a country in West Africa. Before the French came in and ruined everything, there was a region in Benin known as the Kingdom of Dahomey, a kingdom with the best flag ever: an elephant with a crown. The unrelated Kingdom of Benin, which is/was in present day Nigeria, also has a great flag.

food.name: Peanut Soup
food.description: It's got sweet potatoes, it's got coconut milk, it's got peanut butter, it's got spices, it's got soup. A very creamy soup that combines sweet and savory perfectly.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
You can't make an omelet without breaking a few eggs, and you can't make a peanut soup without breaking a few peanuts.

food.name: Wagasi in Sauce
food.description: It's probably a cop-out to substitute wagasi cheese in a recipe literally called 'wagasi in sauce' but if you can find me a place to buy actual wagasi cheese in North America, you let me know and I will remake this recipe with the real thing. It was still tasty, though, as fried things and cheeses tend to be.

diet.description: It's literally cheese.

music.name: Angélique Kidjo - Once In A Lifetime

BT.name: Bhutan
BT.description: The Kingdom of Bhutan is a country in South Asia ruled by the Dragon King. As of November 2021, the current Dragon King - Jigme Khesar Namgyel Wangchuck - is the second youngest monarch in the world at 41 years old, after Rukidi IV of Toro, who is 29.

food.name: Ema Datshi
food.description: Cheese. Pepper. Rice. These were the ingredients chosen to create the perfect rice dish. Spiciness and cheesiness are a great combination.

diet.description: One of the main ingredients is chili peppers. You can use whatever peppers you want (even bell peppers) to get a spiciness amount you are comfortable with.
Butter and cheese are used in this dish.

food.name: Momo
food.description: Hard to go wrong with steamed dumplings full of cheese. As soon as I master the art of folding and wrapping dumplings into various shapes you can bet your ass I'm gonna make a million YouTube videos abeut it.

diet.description: Flour is used in the dough.
Cheese is used in these cheese dumplings.

Yeshi Bidha ft. Kezang Dorji - Gokab

They recently legalized stoning as a punishment for being gay, so, y'know, now's a good time to donate to an organization like Rainbow Railroad.

BG.description: The Republic of Bulgaria is a country in Southeast Europe. As of 2018, it was the most corrupt country in the European Union, which is pretty impressive given the rest of the European Union.

food.name: Garash Cake
food.description: A delicious *gluten-free* cake made almost entirely of walnuts, sugar, and eggs. It is very sweet, which is always a good thing when eating sweets. That's why they're called sweets, after all.

diet.description: Walnuts are the main ingredient in this cake's batter.
Butter and heavy whipping cream are used in the ganache frosting.

food.description: You cook up some spiced meats and potatoes, then you pour some milky eggs on top and cook it all a bit more, and you get a custard-topped dream come true. I posted this with the hashtag "custard" on social media (alongside several other joke hashtags like #grungo and #spaghettiHyperloop) and then some frozen custard company store in Milwaukee followed me and commented "what's up?" Buddy, this is not the kind of custard you're looking for.

BF.name: Burkina Faso
BF.description: Burkina Faso is a country in West Africa. They were French, then there were a handful of coup d'états, then Thomas Sankara came in and did a lot of revolutionary and Marxist things that made a lot of people happy and a few people with guns mad, so he got assassinated. So then the assassination guy ruled the country for a few decades, then fled the country in 2014 after people got mad at him for trying to remove term limits. In 2021 he was indicted for the murder of Sankara and the trial began in October. Only took 34 years!

BI.name: Burundi
BI.description: The Republic of Burundi is a small country between East and Central Africa. Less than a fifth of the population lives in urban areas, and the majority of the citizens belong to one of three tribes: the Hutu, Tutsi, and Twa.

food.name: Anise Bread
food.description: Fun fact: anise just tastes exactly like (black) licorice. Which means this bread just tastes like licorice. If you're a fan of licorice, you'll like this bread. If you're not, you still might like it anyway! I hate licorice and I still thought this bread was pretty good.

CV.name: Cabo Verde
CV.description: The Republic of Cabo Verde is an island country west of continental Africa. They have declared that their official English name is "Cabo Verde" but that doesn't stop people from calling it "Cape Verde" still because calling things by their names is hard apparently. It consists of ten islands whose geography contributes to powerful hurricanes that travel west to hit the Americas. <s>Maybe they'll stop once Americans start getting their name right.</s>

food.name: Bolinhos de mandioca com mel
food.description: So this recipe is in Portuguese and omits several important things like the amount of flour to use and the baking time and temperature, so I had to improvise. And use wheat flour since I ran out of cassava flour. So I probably didn't ACTUALLY make this dish, but I made something probably similar perhaps, and it was still tasty! So, hoorah. If you want to make whatever the hell I made, follow this recipe but then keep adding flour until it forms a batter, then cook at 185 degrees Celcius for 15 minutes.

KH.name: Cambodia
KH.description: The Kingdom of Cambodia is a country in Southeast Asia. They had some bad times, as many countries that got colonized did, including four years of extremely bad times (genocide), but now things are slowly getting better! Unfortunately, there are still a lot of landmines scattered throughout the country, making progress difficult. Fortunately, many efforts have been undertaken to address this, including the deployment of Gambian pouched rats, who can smell land mines.

food.name: Chicken Amok
food.description: You know what's always good and never bad? Curry. You know what this is? Curry. It's good. The lemongrass and mint give it a very fresh cool flavor that complements the spiciness very well. A crowd-pleaser.

diet.description: This is a chicken curry, but you can use fish or pretty much whatever you want that is good in a curry.

food.name: Lok Lak
food.description: A very tasty marinade and fancy dipping sauce brings this meat into true Yum In My Tum territory. I only burned the meat a little bit! Well, a little bit, total. No burning on one side and a lotta burning on the other. Still tasty! Shout out to Marcin for finding this recipe while I was busy panicking about how every Cambodian dish I could find was seafood-based. Surprise, now you know why none of the recipes on this site are fish dishes!

diet.description: This is a steak dish. Chicken broth powder is used in the marinade as well.
The beef marinade and the sauce use fish sauce, which can be substituted with an anchovy-free Worcestershire sauce if you don't do the fish thing.
The beef marinade uses soy sauce, which can be substituted with coconut aminos and everything will be A-OK.

CM.name: Cameroon
CM.description: The Republic of Cameroon is a country in Central Africa. Its diverse climates range from beaches to deserts to rainforests to mountains. As someone who comes from a region where the two seasons are "warm" and "slightly less warm," the thought of this amazes me.

food.name: Koki Corn
food.description: I'd literally never seen a tamale before in my life until this. Which is strange because I live in California, but somehow I lived 29 years never seeing or eating an actual tamale. But I guess this is an actual tamale. And it was good. Therefore, tamales are good.

A lot of people think it's a really good country and everyone is nice, but when your neighbor is basically just a slightly more racist and violent version of you, it's not hard to see why. Despite being the second largest country in the world, it isn't even in the top 30 most populated, because a lot of that land is just way too cold.

food.name: Butter Tart

That joke was to lighten the mood, because as of this writing (November 2021), there is an ongoing civil war in the country, and it is one of the poorest nations in the world. The joke was necessary because if you read more about this country elsewhere, you're not going to find much in the way of good news. Colonialism is bad and does lasting damage to former colonies, everybody.

food.name: Fulani Boullie
food.description: This is what happens when you get peanut butter and rice, like that one Reese's Peanut Butter Cup commercial but one guy just has a huge vat of rice or something. Burnt peanut butter may be permanently stuck on one of my pots.

food.description: The pumpkin seed powder mixed into the meatballs gave them a pretty wild flavor that was guaranteed goodtimes for my mouth. I usually just buy frozen meatballs on the rare occassion I need meatballs, but next time I may just make these instead.

They're going through some bad times, and one of the websites I grabbed a recipe from had this, so here's a listing of several Chad-related NGOs you can donate to. In April 2021, their president of 31 years was assassinated, so hopefully things will change for the better with a new government.

food.name: Bouillie
food.description: I realized moments after making this that the dish was very similar to the fulani boullie I made for the Central African Republic. But it's definitely a completely different peanut butter rice porridge dish, so it's okay. Don't worry about it. This one didn't ruin my saucepan, so I like it more.

For a while they were ruled by the Pinochet dictatorship, which is a bad thing unless you're one of those dipshits who share helicopter memes on social media in which case please leave this website and learn how to be a decent human. Fortunately, he's dead now and Chile is one of the most prosperous countries in South America, and has the second lowest homicide rate in the Americas after Canada.

food.name: Conejos
food.description: Dulce de leche is the perfect food, and sweet pastry buns are the perfect container for food. Thus, a combination of the two is a beautiful thing.

CN.name: China
CN.description: The People's Republic of China is a country in East Asia. By pretty much every metric, it is what one might call "very big." I think it's safe to say you probably know a thing or two about China, and it is possible that you are waiting for me to give an opinion about China's government so you can argue with me. Well, guess what? I agree with you on every issue about China, so take that! Well, except all the ones you're wrong about. But everything else? I agree 100%.

food.name: Básī dìguā (Shandong cuisine)
food.description: If you wanty eat some sweet potatos but are disappointed with how they aren't as sweet as their name might suggest, you can try frying them and then stirring them into a very hot sugar syrup. Then you can VERY CAREFULLY pull a sticky stringy chunk of sweet potato out of the pile, dip it into some ice water to cool and solidify the hot sugar, and then crunch into yum!

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

food.name: Coconut Bar (Cantonese cuisine)

diet.description: The ingredients in this dish vary, but one of the ingredients that's pretty much 100% necessary is tofu.

Shrimp is another common ingredient. But, again, you can just put whatever you want in this soup.

food.name: Dong'an Chicken (Hunan cuisine)
food.description: I can't tell if my spice tolerance is increasing or if I'm just underspicing things subconsciously because I am a baby. Probably the second one. Either way, very tasty chicken.

food.description: As a disclaimer, I don't actually like pork. This dish did not change my mind. I also probably cooked this dish wrong because I've never cooked pork before and it was harder than expected to find pork belly. Having said all that... s'fine. 'Sa fine dish. Probably better if you can find pork belly that isn't pre-sliced and you actually like pork, but even without that, s'fine.

food.description: These are basically just tiny omelets. Which is not a bad thing, if you like omelets. Omelets covered in soy sauce.

food.name: Carimañolas

food.name: Pandebonos

I'm really tired right now because it's 1am so I should probably wait until later to write this but in my sleep-deprived state I feel like I'm qualified to speak my emotions and my emotions for these cheesy bread babies are nothing but positive ones. KM.description: The Union of the Comoros is a country in the Indian Ocean. It consists of several small islands, 3 main islands, and maybe one other main island, but that island is still under French rule so, y'know, there's that whole thing going on.

food.name: Ladu
food.description: Balls of cooked rice, sugar, cardamom, black pepper, and ghee. I will go on the record and say that I burnt the rice a bit, or a lot. It tasted like sweet burnt rice. Bone App the Teeth.

diet.description: Ghee is used to help things stick together.

food.name: Pilaou au Poulet
food.description: Rice + Spice = Nice. This is the formula for a good number of dishes I've cooked so far and this dish is just more proof of its correctness. It makes a yumyum in my tumtum, with special note given to the nice carmelized onions in every bite.

diet.description: You can beef or chicken this dish.
Fermented butter is used in this dish.

CG.name: Congo-Brazzaville
CG.description: The Republic of the Congo is a country on the coast of Central Africa. It is the tinier of the two Congos. Why are there two Congos, you ask? Well, the one word answer is "politics." The three word answer is "colonialism and politics." Any more words and you're better off consulting literally any resource that isn't some white dude's cooking and music site.

food.name: Moambé Chicken
food.description: Guess who, just now, as he started writing this, realized that this dish is probably identical to the Moamba de Galinha he made for Angola? This guy! Fortunately, the two recipes are pretty different as this one called for peanut butter as the prize ingredient as opposed to the Angolan version's palm oil. When trying to find recipes for this, I found an article that, in the comments, had a Congolese person angrily stating that the peanut butter recipe was bullshit and that the authentic Congolese version was very different. Sadly, I can no longer find her version because that website up and fucking vanished in the like three days between me finding it and me trying to make this. The site itself exists in the Wayback Machine but the recipe page was not saved, so, whoopsie! Either way, I don't think I like peanut butter chicken. I think that Congolese woman's recipe was probably better.

diet.description: Just make Moabé Tofu if you don't eat chicken.
A wee bit spicy. Not too bad though. Just don't add the red peppie flakes if you don't wanty spice up your life.
Peanut butter is used in the sauce.

food.name: Yassa Chicken
food.description: In my adventures in foreign foods, I am also discovering not-very-foreign-at-all things that I have somehow never tried before. Like mustard. Yeah, I've never had mustard before. Yes at the time of this writing I was a 29 year old U.S. American. Unfortunately, I have now reached the conclusion that I do not like mustard with chicken. This is unfortunate because this is chicken in a mustard sauce.

diet.description: Just make Yassa Tofu if you don't eat chicken.
Scotch Bonnet Peppers or cayenne powder are used. Adjust to your taste.

music.name: Bisso na Bisso - Show ce soir

CD.name: Congo-Kinshasa
CD.description: The Democratic Republic of the Congo is a country in Central Africa and the second largest country in all of Africa. Formerly known as Zaire, they became the Congo in 1997 after the First Congo War ended and the new president declared the name change. It's clear that then-president Laurent Kabila knew that people like me would be doing shit like this in alphabetical order in the future, hence the move from Z up to C.

food.name: Fumbwa
food.description: It smells better than it tastes and it tastes better than it looks. But it also smells like peanut butter, though, which is always a plus.

diet.description: This recipe calls for red palm oil. Please make sure you are buying sustainable palm oil if you make this recipe.
This recipe calls for a chicken stock cube, but you can use a vegetarian stock like I did without issue.
Peanuts are used in this dish.
This recipe calls for smoked catfish. If you're like me and don't eat that sort of thing, you can omit it.

food.name: Mikate
food.description: A crispy slightly coconutty outside with a soft fluffy vanilla-ey inside. Such a simple dough creates such a beautiful treat.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
Flour is used in the dough.

CK.name: Cook Islands
CK.description: The Cook Islands are an island country in the Pacific Ocean. They are in Free Association with New Zealand, which, summarized (to the best of my abilities) means New Zealand is in charge of some things like defense, and all Cook Islands citizens are New Zealand citizens - but not the other way around! According to Wikipedia they're sovereign states, which is good enough for me. They're currently planning on changing the name of the country, since being named after James Cook - the British cartographer who first mapped the islands and then got killed by Hawai'ians after trying to kidnap their king - is not something a lot of Cook Islanders like.

food.name: Curried PawPaw Salad + Dressing
food.description: Tasted like papayas, mayonnaise, and curry powder. Which is not three things I'd usually want to taste at the same time. This is no exception.

diet.description: Mayonnaise is used in the salad.
Honey can be used in the dressing.

food.name: Poke
food.description: This is basically just a creamy papaya pudding. If you like papayas and pudding, this is the thing for you. If you don't like either of those things, maybe don't make this. That's the lesson I learned here.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

Melissa Gosselin - Rarotonga Ipukarea / Just One Look

CR.name: Costa Rica
CR.description: The Republic of Costa Rica is a country in Central America. They are the largest country in the world to not have a military, which they abolished after their last war in 1948, and then allocated their military budget to healthcare and education. Weirdly, Costa Rica has some of the highest literacy rates and life expectancies in Latin America. Hmm... replacing their military budget with funding for education and healthcare, and then their people are very well educated and healthy... WONDER IF THERE'S ANY CORRELATION THERE. I SAID, I WONDER IF THERE'S ANY CORRELATION THERE. I WONDER IF THERE'S ANY--

food.name: Picadillo de Papa
food.description: A hash of potatoes and meat, but mostly potatoes, which are the real winner of any recipe including potatoes. The seasonings were good times. The potatoes were good times. It was all good times.

diet.description: It's a mince dish. You can substitute with fake beef and/or also skip the bacon. Or just go full potato.
Some red peppers are in the recipe, but no one's judging you if you just use bell peppers.

food.name: Proprietary Ice Cream Sandwich
food.description: Graham crackery and ice creamy. Hard to go wrong with that, unless ice cream gives you a brain freeze. Which it does for me, but, hey, the cookies were still tasty!

diet.description: Both the cookies and ice cream call for eggies.
Ice cream. You can use a vegan ice cream instead.
Graham crackers usually have gluten in them. If you can find/make gluten free ones, go for it!

CI.name: Côte d'Ivoire
CI.description: The Côte d'Ivoire is a country in West Africa. Lots of English-speaking people call it "Ivory Coast" because speaking French is apparently too hawd for their widdle baby moufs. The official English name is "Côte d'Ivoire!" They produce a lot of cocoa and coffee, and used to export a lot of that one thing that comes from elephant tusks. You know, the hard white material. I can't remember the name right now.

food.name: Kedjenou Chicken
food.description: The combination of spices here makes for some smooth chickens. Definitely tasty.

diet.description: Kedjenou CHICKEN. You can use tofu maybe I dunno. I'm no tofuologist.
Habanero is optional don't worry.

food.name: Riz au Gras
food.description: It's tomatoey rice. With some beef and shrampies in it. Or no shrampies if you were lazy like me. Still tasty.

diet.description: It's got stew beef.

HR.name: Croatia
HR.description: The Republic of Croatia is a country in Central-Southeast Europe. They got a lot of shoreline and over a thousand islands but a lot of them are very tiny and unpopulated but that doesn't mean you can't jokingly claim one as your own country and then get arrested for it. Yes that is a thing that has happened before and will happen again as soon as I can safely travel here.

food.name: Kremšnita
food.description: A fluffy creamy combination of custardy whippedcreamy puffpastry-y goodness.

diet.description: Flour is used in the dough.

Rum is used in the filling. This can be omitted.

food.name: Povitica
food.description: A tasty spiraly bread with a very pretty cross-section and a very tasty eat-section. Flavors of walnuts, lemons, and vanillis mix well with the soft fluffy bread.

diet.description: Flour is used in the dough.
This is a walnut bread.

Butter and milk are used in the filling and dough.

CU.name: Cuba
CU.description: The Republic of Cuba is an island country in North America. They have excellent healthcare and education, but this is bad actually because good things are only good if the USA does them, I guess.

food.name: Pastelitos de Guayaba
food.description: It's pastry full of guava paste and cream cheese. That's what I call a good food to eat in your mouth. Sweet and a bit savory.

diet.description: Butter is used in puff pastry dough. Cream cheese is used in the filling.
Flour is used in puff pastry dough.
You can put an egg wash on top, but you don't have to.

food.name: Yuca con Ajo
food.description: Tastes like potatoes and garlic, with some acidity from the citrus juices. A tasty treat made slightly less delicious by my anxieties about getting cyanide poisoning from eating undercooked cassava.

diet.description: Cassava must be cooked thoroughly to remove the cyanide.
This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.

Krudas Cubensi - En el Solar
music.translation: Krudas Cubensi - In the Building Plot

CY.name: Cyprus
CY.description: The Republic of Cyprus is an island country in the eastern Mediterranean Sea in Europe. There's a Greek half and a Turkish half and according to my half-assed internet searches, the consensus among many of them seems to be that reunification seems like it'd be cool. Turkey, however, may disagree. What, you want my opinion? I've never even been to Europe, why the hell should my opinion on this matter at all? I think they should unify and change their name to Ultra Cyprus and donate 10% of their GDP to me. How's that sound to you? Is that what you wanted? IS THAT WHAT YOU WANTED?? The opinions of someone who will literally never be affected by the issue at hand, with no first-hand, or even second-hand knowledge of it??! Let the Cypriots handle it!! I'm a honkey-ass Californian! I'm just eating their food, not solving their decades-long political struggles!!

food.name: Hellimli
food.description: This is a very intense bread full of lots of flavors and textures in every bite. If you can handle its power, you will find a very delicious, cheesy, and filling bread.

diet.description: Bread. It uses flour. Sorry.
Melk is used in the dough. Oh, yeah, also cheese. It's a cheese bread. Full of cheese.

food.name: Shiamishi
food.description: Happy Feast Day of Kosmas and Damianos! To celebrate like the Orthodox Cypriots might, whip up some wet flour that has been wrapped around some wetter, different flour, and then fried! The result? Pretty tasty!

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
It's made of flour and it's filled with flour.

CZ.name: Czechia
CZ.description: The Czech Republic is a country in Central Europe. They have the lowest unemployment rate in the European Union and they drink the most beer per capita in the world. Coincidence? Normally I'd say yes, since you should all know by now that correlation does not imply causation, but I've been sort of doing a running gag in these country descriptions where I say, like, "oh this country does these obviously good things and also has all of these good attributes I wonder if they're related" so, in keeping with that theme, I will instead say: not coincidence! The takeaway you should get from this is that beer causes employment.

food.name: Česnečka
food.description: A very hearty, very garlicky soup. Especially if you use more than double the recommended amount of garlic like I did. What? It's literally a garlic soup. I ain't gonty skimp out on the GARLIC. But it was delicious. Cured all my ailments and status effects.

diet.description: Butter can be used to fry the onions, but you can also use oil. Grated cheese is an optional topping.
This uses chicken or beef broth, but you can use a vegetarian broth. Lard can be used to fry the onions.

food.name: Knedlíky
food.description: It's like bread... but boiled. So it kind tastes and feels like wet bread. Since it's not baked, it lacks that distinct Maillard reaction flavor that bread usually has. Very good for soaking up soup, though!

diet.description: Milk is used in the dough.

DK.name: Denmark
DK.description: The Kingdom of Denmark is a Nordic country in Northern Europe. They have been to war with Sweden very many times "for little or no political reason," to quote Wikipedia. The kingdom spans the country of Denmark itself, as well as the Faroe Islands and Greenland. Two more completely unrelated fun facts about Denmark: they are one of the most heavily taxed countries in the world and one of the happiest countries in the world.

food.name: Boller i Karry
food.description: If anyone was expecting a Scandinavian curry to be mind-blowing, it wasn't me, and for good reason. I mean, it's curry, so it's still delicious, but apple isn't a thing I'd have thought to put into curry, and I was right to not think that.

diet.description: It's got meatballs.
Egg is used to bind the meatballs.
Milk is used in meatballs.
Flour is used to bind the meatballs and thicken the curry sauce.
Could be spicy, depending on the curry powder you use.

food.name: Vaniljekranse
food.description: What us Americans know as the delicious butter cookies from the blue tins that are often full of sewing supplies, are actually just delicious butter cookies... from Denmark! Trying to get the ring shape failed after my piping bag burst, so I settled for making several in regular disk shapes. Still delicious!

diet.description: Flour is used in the dough.
Butter is used in the dough.
Egg is used in the dough.
Almond flour is used in the dough.

DJ.name: Djibouti
DJ.description: The Republic of Djibouti is a country in Northeast Africa, in the Horn of Africa. If you wanna get to the Red Sea, you gotta go by Djibouti, so it's a hoppin' place to be for shipping ships. And also military bases because what good is a gulf if you can't kill people around it?

food.name: Lahooh
food.description: Spongy bread. Soaks up broth and such very well, but extremely bland on its own.

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
It's bread.

food.name: Skoudehkaris
food.description: A soupy rice bowl that's fun for the whole family. This recipe calls for cardamom pods and doesn't specify to grind them up first, so I got a few bites of cardamom that were P U R E F L A V O R.

diet.description: It's meaty rice.

music.name: Hani Uk - Korkayga Bal Taabo a Naaji

DM.name: Dominica
DM.description: The Commonwealth of Dominica is an island country in the West Indies. It's one of two countries to use the color purple on its flag, as their national bird - the lovely and purple sisserou parrot - is in the center of it.

food.name: Callaloo Soup
food.description: A creamy green soup. I used spinach because I could not find callaloo, which seems like a sin given the name of the dish, but the recipe itself says spinach is a valid substitute, so I'm innocent of all crimes!

diet.description: This dish is vegan-friendly without any substitutions.
It's got scotch bonnet or habanero peppie in it, but you can also just not do that.

food.name: Cush Cush Biscuits
food.description: Some nice slightly sweet slightly savory biscuits. Good in my book.

DO.name: Dominican Republic
DO.description: The Dominican Republic is country in the Caribbean. Christopher Columbus - the bastard man who didn't discover shit - did a lot of genocide here. Now they're a big hotspot in the Caribbean, sharing their island with Haiti - a country they don't hate now but wowie do not look up Rafael Trujillo if the thought of Dominicans and Haitians being friends is very important to you.

food.name: Domplines
food.description: Basically pasta but the dough has butter in it so it's not technically a pasta dough. The bell pepper and cheddar sauce was very tasty, too. I've got a bunch left over to use on macaroni later!

diet.description: They got cheese, milk, and butter in the sauce. Butter is also used in the dough.

food.description: Delicious dumples. The fried bulghur shells provided a unique texture that was definitely appreciated.

Ground beef is the main filling, but you can replace it with like chickpeas or something. There's a link to a vegan baked version in the linked recipe.

food.name: Morir Soñando
food.description: Milky, orangey, tasty. But if you're going to follow this recipe, don't add any sugar until after you've tasted it without any first because wowie was that too much sugar.

EC.name: Ecuador
EC.description: The Republic of Ecuador is a country in northwest South America. It is the first country to give constitutional rights to nature, which, given how badly some countries are destroying the environment, is probably a pretty good idea.

food.name: Humitas
food.description: Tastes like corn and cheese, because that's largely what it is. Pretty good vehicle to deliver corn and cheese to your mouth.

diet.description: Heavy cream is used in the dough.

food.name: Llapingachos
food.description: It's hard to go wrong with a recipe that's mostly fried potatoes, sauteed onions, and melted cheese. Empires were built on that combination of ingredients.

Flour can be added to keep things stuck together, but you can also use a gluten-free starch for binding, or none at all!

food.description: A savory and slightly sweet peanut sauce that goes very well with the cheesy fried llapingachos.

diet.description: Peanut sauce. Come on. Don't make this if you have a peanut allergy. You can't sue me, it won't work.
Milk is used in the sauce, and butter can be used to cook the onions. You can use coconut milk or something, it'll be fine.
You can put a hard-boiled egg in it if you want to.
You can add a hot pepper if you want to.

EG.name: Egypt
EG.description: The Arab Republic of Egypt is a country in Northeast Africa. It's obviously well-known for, like, all of the pyramids and heiroglyphs and mythology, and just generally being one of the oldest - if not the oldest - civilizations. If you want to know more, I recommend doing some actual research, or, if you're too lazy for that, check out the educational beekeeping video game, Beegypt, that I made in August 2019. It's free, probably at least mostly historically accurate, and has bees!

food.name: Hawawshi
food.description: A hearty and flavorful meal, made more challenging to make and eat due to the fact that that, apparently, Arabic pita has pockets to stuff with meat and Greek pita does not. I wish I had known that before I had bought Greek pita. Even with the challenge of halving pitas manually (and not accidentally cutting myself in the process, hooray!), these were still delicious.

SV.description: The Republic of El Salvador is the smallest country in Central America. Even after their long and bloody civil war ended, they still have the highest murder rate in the world, with most murders related to gang activity. The country also has a lot of volcanos. Unsurprisingly, a lot of the violence - especially during the civil war - can be blamed on the USA. We can, however, safely assume the volcanos are unrelated to US involvement for the time being.

food.name: Atol de Elote
food.description: When I first finished making this, it smelled so much like sweet corn that it worried me. But alas, it tastes very soothing when warm.

food.description: The panela honey I dipped these in was delicious, but perhaps a bit sweet for these very salty fritters.

food.name: Pupusas
food.description: Extremely delicious and Very Yum. The crispy corny exterior blends perfectly with the creamy cheesy interior. The fermented cabbage and onion topping - curtido - gave it an excellent tanginess as well.

diet.description: Extremely full of cheese. You could put beans inside instead. There's no wrong way to fill a pupusa.

GQ.name: Equatorial Guinea
GQ.description: The Republic of Equatiorial Guinea is a country in western Central Africa. It is the sole Spanish-speaking country in Africa, and as of November 2021, has had the same president since 1979. ¡Dios mio!

food.name: Ginger Millet Porridge
food.description: I am generally skeptical of porridges or any foods with the texture of "not quite liquid, not quite solid," but the cinnamonny gingery flavor of this was a pleasant surprise. Good Flavor Combo/10.

food.name: Ginja Beer
food.description: This tastes like ginger and yeast. I was too afraid of the bottle exploding while it was fermenting so I kept opening the bottle to let gas out, so the end result was a bit flat. Still tasted fine, though.

food.name: Nkate Cake
food.description: Nothing too exciting to say about this one. Do you like peanuts? Do you like sugar? If so, you'll like this. It's basically just peanut brittle. You like that, you'll like this.

ER.name: Eritrea
ER.description: The State of Eritrea is a country in East Africa. It was one of the few African countries colonized by Italy, and was part of Ethiopia for a while because the Allies (from World War II) were like "hey yeah we don't know what to do with Eritrea now that the Italians are gone so let's make it part of Ethiopia!" The Eritreans didn't like that. After a 40-year war that led to hundreds of thousands of deaths (mostly Eritrean civilians), they finally regained their independence in 1991.
ER.languages: English, Arabic, Tigrinya, Beja, Tigre, Kunama, Saho, Bilen, Nara, Afar

food.name: Tsebhi Sega
food.description: I've never had ground lamb before this but this was delicious as hell, so consider me a fan. I will remember lamb favorably and definitely try using these spice combinations again in other dishes in the future.

food.name: Zigni Spaghetti
food.description: Mamma mia! That's a spicy pasta! This reminds me a lot of pasta arrabbiata in that they're both spicy tomato sauces, but using berbere seasoning instead of just chili peppers makes it slightly less spicy but significantly more flavorful.
